# AI Governance

## Ownership

- This codebase is **100% AI-maintained**. Implement, refactor, document, and changelog all changes via AI.
- The human user directs work in Korean chat only.

## Language

- **User replies**: Korean only — **plain words, as short as possible** (see `.cursor/rules/brief-korean-replies.mdc`).
- **Code, comments, docs, rules, changelog, handover**: English only.
- **In-app UI**: Korean via `tr()` / `QStringLiteral`. Keep JSON block `type` values in English.

## User preference profile (mandatory — cumulative in AGENTS.md only)

- **Read** [AGENTS.md §9.5](../../AGENTS.md#95-user-preference-profile-cumulative--agents-only) at **task start** before UI, workflow, docs, or architecture choices.
- **Append** dated bullets in §9.5 **same task** when the user states or clearly implies work style, aesthetics, collaboration habits, or anti-preferences — **never** a separate `USER_*.md` file; **never delete** prior §9.5 bullets.
- If a preference must constrain every future agent, add a **one-line pointer** here or in `immediate-handover.mdc`; full wording stays in §9.5.

## Regression mistake log (오답노트 — mandatory for multi-attempt bugs)

- After a **user-confirmed** fix for a bug that took multiple wrong attempts, append an entry to [AGENTS.md §9.6](../../AGENTS.md#96-regression-mistake-log-오답노트--agents-only) in the **same task**: symptom, failed approaches (with version refs), root cause, shipped symbols.
- Add or extend **§8.x** mandatory pattern + `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` when agents must not regress the fix; §9.6 records **why earlier patches failed**.

## After Every Completed Task

1. Append entries under `[Unreleased]` in **AGENTS.md** section **11. Changelog and Version History** as you implement.
2. If this chat surfaced preference signal not yet in §9.5, append it there before close.
3. **Before closing the task:** bump version per **AGENTS.md** §10 — update `CMakeLists.txt`, move `[Unreleased]` into `## [x.y.z] - YYYY-MM-DD`, add Korean section to **`UpdateLog/update_log.md`** (§3.7), leave empty `[Unreleased]`. Then run **`.\scripts\build-release.ps1` only** when C++/headers/`CMakeLists.txt` changed; skip build for docs/rules-only. **Then mandatory backup + GitHub release** per **AGENTS.md** §3.6.
4. Keep diffs minimal; match existing C++ / Qt conventions in surrounding code.

